 370 def parse_example(serialized, names, sparse_keys, dense_keys, dense_defaults, sparse_types, dense_shapes, name=None):
 371   r"""Transforms a vector of brain.Example protos (as strings) into typed tensors.
 372 
 373   Args:
 374     serialized: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 375       A vector containing a batch of binary serialized Example protos.
 376     names: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 377       A vector containing the names of the serialized protos.
 378       May contain, for example, table key (descriptive) names for the
 379       corresponding serialized protos.  These are purely useful for debugging
 380       purposes, and the presence of values here has no effect on the output.
 381       May also be an empty vector if no names are available.
 382       If non-empty, this vector must be the same length as "serialized".
 383     sparse_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
 384       A list of Nsparse string Tensors (scalars).
 385       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with sparse values.
 386     dense_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
 387       A list of Ndense string Tensors (scalars).
 388       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with dense values.
 389     dense_defaults: A list of `Tensor` objects with types from: `float32`, `int64`, `string`.
 390       A list of Ndense Tensors (some may be empty).
 391       dense_defaults[j] provides default values
 392       when the example's feature_map lacks dense_key[j].  If an empty Tensor is
 393       provided for dense_defaults[j], then the Feature dense_keys[j] is required.
 394       The input type is inferred from dense_defaults[j], even when it's empty.
 395       If dense_defaults[j] is not empty, and dense_shapes[j] is fully defined,
 396       then the shape of dense_defaults[j] must match that of dense_shapes[j].
 397       If dense_shapes[j] has an undefined major dimension (variable strides dense
 398       feature), dense_defaults[j] must contain a single element:
 399       the padding element.
 400     sparse_types: A list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`.
 401       A list of Nsparse types; the data types of data in each Feature
 402       given in sparse_keys.
 403       Currently the ParseExample supports DT_FLOAT (FloatList),
 404       DT_INT64 (Int64List), and DT_STRING (BytesList).
 405     dense_shapes: A list of shapes (each a `tf.TensorShape` or list of `ints`).
 406       A list of Ndense shapes; the shapes of data in each Feature
 407       given in dense_keys.
 408       The number of elements in the Feature corresponding to dense_key[j]
 409       must always equal dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().
 410       If dense_shapes[j] == (D0, D1, ..., DN) then the shape of output
 411       Tensor dense_values[j] will be (|serialized|, D0, D1, ..., DN):
 412       The dense outputs are just the inputs row-stacked by batch.
 413       This works for dense_shapes[j] = (-1, D1, ..., DN).  In this case
 414       the shape of the output Tensor dense_values[j] will be
 415       (|serialized|, M, D1, .., DN), where M is the maximum number of blocks
 416       of elements of length D1 * .... * DN, across all minibatch entries
 417       in the input.  Any minibatch entry with less than M blocks of elements of
 418       length D1 * ... * DN will be padded with the corresponding default_value
 419       scalar element along the second dimension.
 420     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 421 
 422   Returns:
 423     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (sparse_indices, sparse_values, sparse_shapes, dense_values).
 424 
 425     sparse_indices: A list with the same length as `sparse_keys` of `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 426     sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `sparse_types`.
 427     sparse_shapes: A list with the same length as `sparse_keys` of `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 428     dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects. Has the same type as `dense_defaults`.
 429   """
 430   _ctx = _context._context
 431   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 432     if not isinstance(sparse_keys, (list, tuple)):
 433       raise TypeError(
 434           "Expected list for 'sparse_keys' argument to "
 435           "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % sparse_keys)
 436     _attr_Nsparse = len(sparse_keys)
 437     if not isinstance(dense_keys, (list, tuple)):
 438       raise TypeError(
 439           "Expected list for 'dense_keys' argument to "
 440           "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % dense_keys)
 441     _attr_Ndense = len(dense_keys)
 442     if not isinstance(sparse_types, (list, tuple)):
 443       raise TypeError(
 444           "Expected list for 'sparse_types' argument to "
 445           "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % sparse_types)
 446     sparse_types = [_execute.make_type(_t, "sparse_types") for _t in sparse_types]
 447     if not isinstance(dense_shapes, (list, tuple)):
 448       raise TypeError(
 449           "Expected list for 'dense_shapes' argument to "
 450           "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % dense_shapes)
 451     dense_shapes = [_execute.make_shape(_s, "dense_shapes") for _s in dense_shapes]
 452     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 453         "ParseExample", serialized=serialized, names=names,
 454         sparse_keys=sparse_keys, dense_keys=dense_keys,
 455         dense_defaults=dense_defaults, sparse_types=sparse_types,
 456         dense_shapes=dense_shapes, name=name)
 457     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 458     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 459     _attrs = ("Nsparse", _op.get_attr("Nsparse"), "Ndense",
 460               _op.get_attr("Ndense"), "sparse_types",
 461               _op.get_attr("sparse_types"), "Tdense", _op.get_attr("Tdense"),
 462               "dense_shapes", _op.get_attr("dense_shapes"))
 463     _execute.record_gradient(
 464       "ParseExample", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 465     _result = [_result[:_attr_Nsparse]] + _result[_attr_Nsparse:]
 466     _result = _result[:1] + [_result[1:1 + len(sparse_types)]] + _result[1 + len(sparse_types):]
 467     _result = _result[:2] + [_result[2:2 + _attr_Nsparse]] + _result[2 + _attr_Nsparse:]
 468     _result = _result[:3] + [_result[3:]]
 469     _result = _ParseExampleOutput._make(_result)
 470     return _result
 471 
 472   else:
 473     try:
 474       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
 475         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name, "ParseExample",
 476         name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks, serialized, names, sparse_keys,
 477         dense_keys, dense_defaults, "sparse_types", sparse_types,
 478         "dense_shapes", dense_shapes)
 479       _result = _ParseExampleOutput._make(_result)
 480       return _result
 481     except _core._FallbackException:
 482       return parse_example_eager_fallback(
 483           serialized, names, sparse_keys, dense_keys, dense_defaults,
 484           sparse_types=sparse_types, dense_shapes=dense_shapes, name=name,
 485           ctx=_ctx)
 486     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
 487       if name is not None:
 488         message = e.message + " name: " + name
 489       else:
 490         message = e.message

 494 def parse_example_eager_fallback(serialized, names, sparse_keys, dense_keys, dense_defaults, sparse_types, dense_shapes, name=None, ctx=None):
 495   r"""This is the slowpath function for Eager mode.
 496   This is for function parse_example
 497   """
 498   _ctx = ctx if ctx else _context.context()
 499   if not isinstance(sparse_keys, (list, tuple)):
 500     raise TypeError(
 501         "Expected list for 'sparse_keys' argument to "

 504   if not isinstance(dense_keys, (list, tuple)):
 505     raise TypeError(
 506         "Expected list for 'dense_keys' argument to "
 507         "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % dense_keys)
 508   _attr_Ndense = len(dense_keys)
 509   if not isinstance(sparse_types, (list, tuple)):
 510     raise TypeError(
 511         "Expected list for 'sparse_types' argument to "
 512         "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % sparse_types)
 513   sparse_types = [_execute.make_type(_t, "sparse_types") for _t in sparse_types]
 514   if not isinstance(dense_shapes, (list, tuple)):
 515     raise TypeError(
 516         "Expected list for 'dense_shapes' argument to "
 517         "'parse_example' Op, not %r." % dense_shapes)
 518   dense_shapes = [_execute.make_shape(_s, "dense_shapes") for _s in dense_shapes]
 519   _attr_Tdense, dense_defaults = _execute.convert_to_mixed_eager_tensors(dense_defaults, _ctx)
 520   serialized = _ops.convert_to_tensor(serialized, _dtypes.string)
 521   names = _ops.convert_to_tensor(names, _dtypes.string)
 522   sparse_keys = _ops.convert_n_to_tensor(sparse_keys, _dtypes.string)
 523   dense_keys = _ops.convert_n_to_tensor(dense_keys, _dtypes.string)
 524   _inputs_flat = [serialized, names] + list(sparse_keys) + list(dense_keys) + list(dense_defaults)
 525   _attrs = ("Nsparse", _attr_Nsparse, "Ndense", _attr_Ndense, "sparse_types",
 526   sparse_types, "Tdense", _attr_Tdense, "dense_shapes", dense_shapes)
 527   _result = _execute.execute(b"ParseExample", _attr_Nsparse +
 528                              len(sparse_types) + _attr_Nsparse +
 529                              len(dense_defaults), inputs=_inputs_flat,

 531   _execute.record_gradient(
 532       "ParseExample", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)

 536   _result = _result[:3] + [_result[3:]]
 537   _result = _ParseExampleOutput._make(_result)
 538   return _result

 554 def parse_sequence_example(serialized, debug_name, context_dense_defaults, feature_list_dense_missing_assumed_empty, context_sparse_keys, context_dense_keys, feature_list_sparse_keys, feature_list_dense_keys, Ncontext_sparse=0, Ncontext_dense=0, Nfeature_list_sparse=0, Nfeature_list_dense=0, context_sparse_types=[], feature_list_dense_types=[], context_dense_shapes=[], feature_list_sparse_types=[], feature_list_dense_shapes=[], name=None):
 555   r"""Transforms a vector of brain.SequenceExample protos (as strings) into typed tensors.
 556 
 557   Args:
 558     serialized: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 559       A vector containing binary serialized SequenceExample protos.
 560     debug_name: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 561       A vector containing the names of the serialized protos.
 562       May contain, for example, table key (descriptive) name for the
 563       corresponding serialized proto.  This is purely useful for debugging
 564       purposes, and the presence of values here has no effect on the output.
 565       May also be an empty vector if no name is available.
 566     context_dense_defaults: A list of `Tensor` objects with types from: `float32`, `int64`, `string`.
 567       A list of Ncontext_dense Tensors (some may be empty).
 568       context_dense_defaults[j] provides default values
 569       when the SequenceExample's context map lacks context_dense_key[j].
 570       If an empty Tensor is provided for context_dense_defaults[j],
 571       then the Feature context_dense_keys[j] is required.
 572       The input type is inferred from context_dense_defaults[j], even when it's
 573       empty.  If context_dense_defaults[j] is not empty, its shape must match
 574       context_dense_shapes[j].
 575     feature_list_dense_missing_assumed_empty: A list of `strings`.
 576       A vector listing the
 577       FeatureList keys which may be missing from the SequenceExamples.  If the
 578       associated FeatureList is missing, it is treated as empty.  By default,
 579       any FeatureList not listed in this vector must exist in the SequenceExamples.
 580     context_sparse_keys: A list of `strings`.
 581       A list of Ncontext_sparse string Tensors (scalars).
 582       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with context_sparse
 583       values.
 584     context_dense_keys: A list of `strings`.
 585       A list of Ncontext_dense string Tensors (scalars).
 586       The keys expected in the SequenceExamples' context features associated with
 587       dense values.
 588     feature_list_sparse_keys: A list of `strings`.
 589       A list of Nfeature_list_sparse string Tensors
 590       (scalars).  The keys expected in the FeatureLists associated with sparse
 591       values.
 592     feature_list_dense_keys: A list of `strings`.
 593       A list of Nfeature_list_dense string Tensors (scalars).
 594       The keys expected in the SequenceExamples' feature_lists associated
 595       with lists of dense values.
 596     Ncontext_sparse: An optional `int` that is `>= 0`. Defaults to `0`.
 597     Ncontext_dense: An optional `int` that is `>= 0`. Defaults to `0`.
 598     Nfeature_list_sparse: An optional `int` that is `>= 0`. Defaults to `0`.
 599     Nfeature_list_dense: An optional `int` that is `>= 0`. Defaults to `0`.
 600     context_sparse_types: An optional list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`. Defaults to `[]`.
 601       A list of Ncontext_sparse types; the data types of data in
 602       each context Feature given in context_sparse_keys.
 603       Currently the ParseSingleSequenceExample supports DT_FLOAT (FloatList),
 604       DT_INT64 (Int64List), and DT_STRING (BytesList).
 605     feature_list_dense_types: An optional list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`. Defaults to `[]`.
 606     context_dense_shapes: An optional list of shapes (each a `tf.TensorShape` or list of `ints`). Defaults to `[]`.
 607       A list of Ncontext_dense shapes; the shapes of data in
 608       each context Feature given in context_dense_keys.
 609       The number of elements in the Feature corresponding to context_dense_key[j]
 610       must always equal context_dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().
 611       The shape of context_dense_values[j] will match context_dense_shapes[j].
 612     feature_list_sparse_types: An optional list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`. Defaults to `[]`.
 613       A list of Nfeature_list_sparse types; the data types
 614       of data in each FeatureList given in feature_list_sparse_keys.
 615       Currently the ParseSingleSequenceExample supports DT_FLOAT (FloatList),
 616       DT_INT64 (Int64List), and DT_STRING (BytesList).
 617     feature_list_dense_shapes: An optional list of shapes (each a `tf.TensorShape` or list of `ints`). Defaults to `[]`.
 618       A list of Nfeature_list_dense shapes; the shapes of
 619       data in each FeatureList given in feature_list_dense_keys.
 620       The shape of each Feature in the FeatureList corresponding to
 621       feature_list_dense_key[j] must always equal
 622       feature_list_dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().
 623     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 624 
 625   Returns:
 626     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (context_sparse_indices, context_sparse_values, context_sparse_shapes, context_dense_values, feature_list_sparse_indices, feature_list_sparse_values, feature_list_sparse_shapes, feature_list_dense_values, feature_list_dense_lengths).
 627 
 628     context_sparse_indices: A list of `Ncontext_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 629     context_sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `context_sparse_types`.
 630     context_sparse_shapes: A list of `Ncontext_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 631     context_dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects. Has the same type as `context_dense_defaults`.
 632     feature_list_sparse_indices: A list of `Nfeature_list_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 633     feature_list_sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `feature_list_sparse_types`.
 634     feature_list_sparse_shapes: A list of `Nfeature_list_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 635     feature_list_dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `feature_list_dense_types`.

 932 def parse_single_example(serialized, dense_defaults, num_sparse, sparse_keys, dense_keys, sparse_types, dense_shapes, name=None):
 933   r"""Transforms a tf.Example proto (as a string) into typed tensors.
 934 
 935   Args:
 936     serialized: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
 937       A vector containing a batch of binary serialized Example protos.
 938     dense_defaults: A list of `Tensor` objects with types from: `float32`, `int64`, `string`.
 939       A list of Tensors (some may be empty), whose length matches
 940       the length of `dense_keys`. dense_defaults[j] provides default values
 941       when the example's feature_map lacks dense_key[j].  If an empty Tensor is
 942       provided for dense_defaults[j], then the Feature dense_keys[j] is required.
 943       The input type is inferred from dense_defaults[j], even when it's empty.
 944       If dense_defaults[j] is not empty, and dense_shapes[j] is fully defined,
 945       then the shape of dense_defaults[j] must match that of dense_shapes[j].
 946       If dense_shapes[j] has an undefined major dimension (variable strides dense
 947       feature), dense_defaults[j] must contain a single element:
 948       the padding element.
 949     num_sparse: An `int` that is `>= 0`.
 950       The number of sparse features to be parsed from the example. This
 951       must match the lengths of `sparse_keys` and `sparse_types`.
 952     sparse_keys: A list of `strings`. A list of `num_sparse` strings.
 953       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with sparse values.
 954     dense_keys: A list of `strings`.
 955       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with dense
 956       values.
 957     sparse_types: A list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`.
 958       A list of `num_sparse` types; the data types of data in each
 959       Feature given in sparse_keys.
 960       Currently the ParseSingleExample op supports DT_FLOAT (FloatList),
 961       DT_INT64 (Int64List), and DT_STRING (BytesList).
 962     dense_shapes: A list of shapes (each a `tf.TensorShape` or list of `ints`).
 963       The shapes of data in each Feature given in dense_keys.
 964       The length of this list must match the length of `dense_keys`.  The
 965       number of elements in the Feature corresponding to dense_key[j] must
 966       always equal dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().  If dense_shapes[j] ==
 967       (D0, D1, ..., DN) then the shape of output Tensor dense_values[j]
 968       will be (D0, D1, ..., DN): In the case dense_shapes[j] = (-1, D1,
 969       ..., DN), the shape of the output Tensor dense_values[j] will be (M,
 970       D1, .., DN), where M is the number of blocks of elements of length
 971       D1 * .... * DN, in the input.
 972     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 973 
 974   Returns:
 975     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (sparse_indices, sparse_values, sparse_shapes, dense_values).
 976 
 977     sparse_indices: A list of `num_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 978     sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `sparse_types`.
 979     sparse_shapes: A list of `num_sparse` `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
 980     dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects. Has the same type as `dense_defaults`.
 981   """
 982   _ctx = _context._context
 983   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 984     num_sparse = _execute.make_int(num_sparse, "num_sparse")
 985     if not isinstance(sparse_keys, (list, tuple)):
 986       raise TypeError(
 987           "Expected list for 'sparse_keys' argument to "
 988           "'parse_single_example' Op, not %r." % sparse_keys)
 989     sparse_keys = [_execute.make_str(_s, "sparse_keys") for _s in sparse_keys]
 990     if not isinstance(dense_keys, (list, tuple)):
 991       raise TypeError(
 992           "Expected list for 'dense_keys' argument to "
 993           "'parse_single_example' Op, not %r." % dense_keys)
 994     dense_keys = [_execute.make_str(_s, "dense_keys") for _s in dense_keys]
 995     if not isinstance(sparse_types, (list, tuple)):
 996       raise TypeError(
 997           "Expected list for 'sparse_types' argument to "
 998           "'parse_single_example' Op, not %r." % sparse_types)
 999     sparse_types = [_execute.make_type(_t, "sparse_types") for _t in sparse_types]
1000     if not isinstance(dense_shapes, (list, tuple)):
1001       raise TypeError(
1002           "Expected list for 'dense_shapes' argument to "
1003           "'parse_single_example' Op, not %r." % dense_shapes)
1004     dense_shapes = [_execute.make_shape(_s, "dense_shapes") for _s in dense_shapes]
1005     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
1006         "ParseSingleExample", serialized=serialized,
1007         dense_defaults=dense_defaults, num_sparse=num_sparse,
1008         sparse_keys=sparse_keys, dense_keys=dense_keys,
1009         sparse_types=sparse_types, dense_shapes=dense_shapes, name=name)
1010     _result = _op.outputs[:]
1011     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
1012     _attrs = ("num_sparse", _op.get_attr("num_sparse"), "sparse_keys",
1013               _op.get_attr("sparse_keys"), "dense_keys",
1014               _op.get_attr("dense_keys"), "sparse_types",
1015               _op.get_attr("sparse_types"), "Tdense", _op.get_attr("Tdense"),
1016               "dense_shapes", _op.get_attr("dense_shapes"))
1017     _execute.record_gradient(
1018       "ParseSingleExample", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
1019     _result = [_result[:num_sparse]] + _result[num_sparse:]
1020     _result = _result[:1] + [_result[1:1 + len(sparse_types)]] + _result[1 + len(sparse_types):]
1021     _result = _result[:2] + [_result[2:2 + num_sparse]] + _result[2 + num_sparse:]
1022     _result = _result[:3] + [_result[3:]]
1023     _result = _ParseSingleExampleOutput._make(_result)
1024     return _result
1025 
1026   else:
1027     try:
1028       _result = _pywrap_tensorflow.TFE_Py_FastPathExecute(
1029         _ctx._context_handle, _ctx._eager_context.device_name,
1030         "ParseSingleExample", name, _ctx._post_execution_callbacks,
1031         serialized, dense_defaults, "num_sparse", num_sparse, "sparse_keys",
1032         sparse_keys, "dense_keys", dense_keys, "sparse_types", sparse_types,
1033         "dense_shapes", dense_shapes)
1034       _result = _ParseSingleExampleOutput._make(_result)
1035       return _result
1036     except _core._FallbackException:
1037       return parse_single_example_eager_fallback(
1038           serialized, dense_defaults, num_sparse=num_sparse,
1039           sparse_keys=sparse_keys, dense_keys=dense_keys,
1040           sparse_types=sparse_types, dense_shapes=dense_shapes, name=name,
1041           ctx=_ctx)
1042     except _core._NotOkStatusException as e:
1043       if name is not None:
1044         message = e.message + " name: " + name
1045       else:
1046         message = e.message
1047       _six.raise_from(_core._status_to_exception(e.code, message), None)

1108 def parse_single_sequence_example(serialized, feature_list_dense_missing_assumed_empty, context_sparse_keys, context_dense_keys, feature_list_sparse_keys, feature_list_dense_keys, context_dense_defaults, debug_name, context_sparse_types=[], feature_list_dense_types=[], context_dense_shapes=[], feature_list_sparse_types=[], feature_list_dense_shapes=[], name=None):
1109   r"""Transforms a scalar brain.SequenceExample proto (as strings) into typed tensors.
1110 
1111   Args:
1112     serialized: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1113       A scalar containing a binary serialized SequenceExample proto.
1114     feature_list_dense_missing_assumed_empty: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1115       A vector listing the
1116       FeatureList keys which may be missing from the SequenceExample.  If the
1117       associated FeatureList is missing, it is treated as empty.  By default,
1118       any FeatureList not listed in this vector must exist in the SequenceExample.
1119     context_sparse_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
1120       A list of Ncontext_sparse string Tensors (scalars).
1121       The keys expected in the Examples' features associated with context_sparse
1122       values.
1123     context_dense_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
1124       A list of Ncontext_dense string Tensors (scalars).
1125       The keys expected in the SequenceExamples' context features associated with
1126       dense values.
1127     feature_list_sparse_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
1128       A list of Nfeature_list_sparse string Tensors
1129       (scalars).  The keys expected in the FeatureLists associated with sparse
1130       values.
1131     feature_list_dense_keys: A list of `Tensor` objects with type `string`.
1132       A list of Nfeature_list_dense string Tensors (scalars).
1133       The keys expected in the SequenceExamples' feature_lists associated
1134       with lists of dense values.
1135     context_dense_defaults: A list of `Tensor` objects with types from: `float32`, `int64`, `string`.
1136       A list of Ncontext_dense Tensors (some may be empty).

1138       when the SequenceExample's context map lacks context_dense_key[j].

1144     debug_name: A `Tensor` of type `string`.
1145       A scalar containing the name of the serialized proto.
1146       May contain, for example, table key (descriptive) name for the
1147       corresponding serialized proto.  This is purely useful for debugging
1148       purposes, and the presence of values here has no effect on the output.
1149       May also be an empty scalar if no name is available.
1150     context_sparse_types: An optional list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`. Defaults to `[]`.

1160       must always equal context_dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().
1161       The shape of context_dense_values[j] will match context_dense_shapes[j].
1162     feature_list_sparse_types: An optional list of `tf.DTypes` from: `tf.float32, tf.int64, tf.string`. Defaults to `[]`.

1165       Currently the ParseSingleSequenceExample supports DT_FLOAT (FloatList),
1166       DT_INT64 (Int64List), and DT_STRING (BytesList).
1167     feature_list_dense_shapes: An optional list of shapes (each a `tf.TensorShape` or list of `ints`). Defaults to `[]`.
1168       A list of Nfeature_list_dense shapes; the shapes of
1169       data in each FeatureList given in feature_list_dense_keys.
1170       The shape of each Feature in the FeatureList corresponding to
1171       feature_list_dense_key[j] must always equal
1172       feature_list_dense_shapes[j].NumEntries().
1173     name: A name for the operation (optional).
1174 
1175   Returns:
1176     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (context_sparse_indices, context_sparse_values, context_sparse_shapes, context_dense_values, feature_list_sparse_indices, feature_list_sparse_values, feature_list_sparse_shapes, feature_list_dense_values).
1177 
1178     context_sparse_indices: A list with the same length as `context_sparse_keys` of `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
1179     context_sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `context_sparse_types`.

1181     context_dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects. Has the same type as `context_dense_defaults`.
1182     feature_list_sparse_indices: A list with the same length as `feature_list_sparse_keys` of `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
1183     feature_list_sparse_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `feature_list_sparse_types`.
1184     feature_list_sparse_shapes: A list with the same length as `feature_list_sparse_keys` of `Tensor` objects with type `int64`.
1185     feature_list_dense_values: A list of `Tensor` objects of type `feature_list_dense_types`.

1190       raise TypeError(
